The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, August 02, 2004  LOOSE CHANGE
																								Allianz Bajaj Life Insurance has unveiled Small Group Term Life Insurance Scheme to protect smaller employer-employee groups ranging from 10 to 50 people. It provides a term cover between Rs 62,000 and Rs 2,00,000. The plan provides accidental benefit along with the basic cover. Customers are also given the option of choosing life cover with Employees Deposit Linked Insurance (EDLI) or non-EDLI.																								Kotak Mutual Fund has launched Kotak Floater Long Term Scheme, an open-ended debt scheme that invests in floating rate debt securities and money market instruments up to 65100 per cent and 0  35 per cent in fixed rate debt securities. The minimum investment amount is Rs 5,000. An exit load of 0.50 per cent will be charged on investments less than Rs 10 lakh if redeemed within six months. The offer will open on August 2 and close on August 6. 																								Hutch and Citibank have launched Hutch Citibank Credit and Debit cards. It will enable customers to place orders and make payments through their Citibank credit card accounts. Card members can earn talk points on purchases, which can be redeemed for free airtime. Other benefits are payment of bills, insurance cover against loss of handset, personal air accident insurance cover of Rs 5 lakh and a 3-month zero per cent EMI scheme for handset purchase at select Hutch shops.
